&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Let&#39;s have fun shaping your future!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are Socialpoint, a world-renowned mobile game studio proudly part of the Zynga &amp;amp; Take-Two Interactive family. We’re the creators of hits like Dragon City, Two Dots, Top Troops, and Monster Legends, loved by hundreds of millions of players around the globe.We craft the best social games, bringing joy from Barcelona to the world. Now, we want to bring the world to Barcelona! At Socialpoint, work and play intertwine seamlessly, and we celebrate the diversity that makes us stronger. No matter who you are or where you’re from, you’re welcome here. Join us for a future where making games is as thrilling as playing them!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Two Dots General Manager, you will be responsible for owning and driving the team setup, product strategy, overall execution and business outcomes. You’ll be asked to balance player experience with commercial success and report on engagement, monetization, marketing and the overall game’s P&amp;amp;L performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With a balance of big-picture thinking and practical execution, you will empower your team to innovate, take risks, learn, and iterate. Ownership, motivation, and strong leadership are essential—your mindset will inspire others to overcome challenges, think differently, and deliver meaningful results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will you do at Socialpoint?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Ownership: &lt;/strong&gt;Own the full P&amp;amp;L with a clear perspective on where to invest for growth vs. optimize. Make explicit trade-offs across UA, LiveOps, and feature development, ensuring every major initiative ties to incremental revenue, margin, or LTV expansion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Vision: &lt;/strong&gt;Define a 12-month product vision that balances core game health (retention, content scalability) with step-change opportunities. Drive a roadmap that avoids incrementalism and instead prioritizes a few high-impact bets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marketing Integration&lt;/strong&gt;: Align product and marketing into a single growth system. Ensure UA, ASO, creatives, and in-game events work together to improve conversion, retention, and payback. Push for faster creative iteration cycles and tighter feedback loops between marketing performance and in-game behavior.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;High-Performance Team Setup: &lt;/strong&gt;Build and develop a crossfuntional A-team (Product, Design, Engineering, Economy, Marketing) that can operate autonomously but stay aligned. Set a high bar for talent density, accountability, and decision-making quality—address underperformance quickly and decisively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Execution Excellence: &lt;/strong&gt;Establish a cadence that connects strategy to delivery: clear goals, tight sprint execution, fast experimentation cycles, and rigorous post-mortems. Reduce organizational drag and ensure the team consistently ships meaningful improvements, not just activity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scalable Processes: &lt;/strong&gt;Design lightweight but effective processes for prioritization, experimentation, and performance tracking. Standardize how decisions are made (data + judgment), how results are measured, and how learnings are shared—so the team compounds knowledge over time instead of relearning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Along with your team, you will be free to innovate, take risks, try, fail, try again, learn &amp;amp; grow. You will have ownership over your own process &amp;amp; you will inspire &amp;amp; be surrounded by inspiring professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
